channel.name: blocktastic-mob-challenge
channel.topic:
Design and build your own unique mob that showcases your creativity! Use any and all blocks in your inventory to bring your creation to life. Is your mob big or small? Does it reside in a large city or roam the forest? Fantastic abilities? You decide!
Challenge dates: April 28 - May 11 at 3 PM PT

messages.content:
Blocktastic mobs (and where to find them) Build Challenge! 💡 + 🖌️ = ❓

Cows with flowers! Snowmen with melon heads! Minecraft Earth is full of unique mobs, but what makes up the blocky DNA of our quirky friends? Imagination of course! Design your own unique mob that showcases your creativity and then build it! Use any and all blocks and items in your inventory to bring your creation to life. Is your mob big or small? Does it reside in a large city or roam the forest? Fantastic abilities? You decide!

:timer: Challenge dates: April 28 - May 11 at 3 PM PT

__Channel Guidelines__
:earth: Your creation must be built entirely by you and in Minecraft Earth.
:crafting_table: Your build must be a brand new creation, crafted just for this challenge.
:buildplate: Build your imagination! Challenge theme is open to interpretation and buildplate size won’t be a factor in judging.
:sign: Post your images or video submission and buildplate share link in #blocktastic-mob-challenge by the deadline. Feel free to ask a Moderator to pin it!
:challenges: Winning submissions may be used in social media posts.
:fast_parrot: Have fun!

Despite being a passive mob, the Wheat Sheep strikes fear to those who deny his believes. 
Tales unfold the mob. Upon them reveal to have said that a mob could produce such nutrients; enough to quench an entire village. It's wool as bright as a Notch apple. It's skin tanner than leather. But with the same rarity of a decent trade with a villager.

Using shears made of the finest glittering gold would you be able to harvest it's enchanted wheat. Upon shearing you earn 1-3 hay bales.
However, upon slaying would the player earn itself... literally just regular mutton. 
As the player, what would your path be?
(ps theyre generally found in the overworld, except with the rarity of finding a pink sheep)

Fun Fact: Minecraft pandas can not only eat bamboo, but cake as well!


__Introducing... the **Pastry Panda**!__

The Pastry Panda loves to eat cake so much that he’s turned into one! This frosting-covered mob is a blast at parties and makes sure to share his sweet treats. He can be found in grass tappables and hangs out near villages since farmers will sometimes give him food.

Feed the Pastry Panda a cake and in return, he’ll give you a random gift! What will you find in his presents?

Unfortunately, hostile mobs don’t know any better and will do anything to take a bite out of him! Build a safe habitat to protect him from monsters.
